title: Human footprints in New Mexico really may be surprisingly ancient, new dating shows
description: Two dating methods find that human tracks in White Sands National Park in New Mexico are roughly 22,000 years old, aligning with a previous estimate.

title: ‘Dormant’ HIV has ongoing skirmishes with the body’s immune system
description: In people on HIV drugs, defective viral bits may still exhaust T cells, possibly making it harder to fight back if people go off the drugs.
